msgid "Return to Arkham"
msgstr "重回阿卡姆"

msgid "Interlude IV: Return to Arkham"
msgstr "幕间故事IV：重回阿卡姆"

msgid "Your sleep on the voyage home is fraught with nightmares. Upon returning to Arkham, you and the others bring the expedition's findings back to an elated Tillinghast. As you relay the events of the expedition to the collector, he turns each piece in hand, marveling at the ancient technology. \"You've done all I asked and more,\" he grins. \"Consider your debts annulled. And, of course, I'm more than happy to honor our original agreement.\""
msgstr "你回家的旅程期间噩梦连连。一到阿卡姆，你和其他人就把探险的发现带给了兴高采烈的蒂林哈斯特。你向这个收藏家讲述了一路探险的故事，他把每样珍宝捏在手里，惊叹于古代的技术。“你做的超出预期。”他狞笑道，“你的债务一笔勾销。当然，我也很乐意履行最初的协议。”"

msgid "Your sleep on the voyage home is fraught with nightmares. Upon returning to Arkham, you and the others lay your few findings before Tillinghast. The antiquarian is furious when he sees you returned empty handed until Andy lays the obsidian slab he found in R'lyeh on his desk. Randall surveys it with a cold stare. \"I suppose this is… adequate. Consider your debts annulled. And, despite the fact that you have brought almost <i>nothing</i> of value, I am obliged to honor our original agreement.\""
msgstr "你回家的旅程期间厘梦连连。一到阿卡姆，你和其他人就把为数不多的成果带给了蒂林哈斯特。古董贩子看到你空手而归，几乎大发雷霆，直到安迪把在拉莱耶发现的黑曜石碑匾放在了他桌上。兰道尔冷眼查看道：“我想这……是足够了。你的债务一笔勾销。还有，尽管你带回来的东西几乎毫无价值，我还是乐意履行最初的协议。”"

msgid "For each progress you have marked on your task, you (and only you) gain 1 additional experience point."
msgstr "你的任务下每记录1点进度，你（且只有你）取得1点奖励经验值。"

msgid "Each investigator resolves his or her corresponding task:"
msgstr "每位调查员结算其对应的任务:"

msgid "This task is complete <i>(it enters play with its <b>Completed</b> side faceup)</i>."
msgstr "本任务已完成<i>（它会以<b>已完成</b>面朝上入场）</i>。"

msgid "If there are 5 or more progress marked under your Task:"
msgstr "如果你的任务下记录了5点或更多的进度："

msgid "Upon returning, you are hailed as a prophet amongst your fellow believers. The dreams that led you to R'lyeh are the same visions shared by your brothers and sisters in the faith. Now, more and more of them are singing in strange tongues and stitching patchwork cloaks. Your purpose in traveling to R'lyeh, in witnessing those lost pilgrims, was not to shake your faith, but to restore it. You have glimpsed the face of the ancients. Only you are fit to lead your people out of darkness and into the light. You need only continue to follow your path with the same unshakeable devotion that delivered you from R'lyeh."
msgstr "你一回城，教中的兄弟姐妹就欢呼你为先知。将你引到拉莱耶的梦境也是他们所见的幻象。现在，越来越多的人开始用奇怪的语言吟唱，开始缝制补丁长袍。你前往拉莱耶，见到那些迷失的朝圣者，不是为了动摇信仰，反而是为了修复信仰。你已经警见远古的真容。只有你才适合领导人民走出黑暗，前往光明。你只需要坚持不可撼动的信仰继续道路，就是这份信仰将你引出了拉莱耶。"

msgctxt "masculine"
msgid "#name# is strong in their faith."
msgstr "#name#信仰坚定。"

msgctxt "feminine"
msgid "#name# is strong in their faith."
msgstr "#name#信仰坚定。"

msgctxt "nonbinary"
msgid "#name# is strong in their faith."
msgstr "#name#信仰坚定。"

msgid ""
"You stand on a bridge overlooking the Miskatonic River, watching the waters below dance and glimmer. Upon returning, you felt something was different. Something changed. Your fellow believers say that outsiders wearing patchwork cloaks recently arrived, uttering miraculous prophecies and enticing promises. Now your place of worship is covered in profane symbols: a hand with a flaming eye; a chalice overflowing with blood. What you once thought holy was ruined."
"Now, as you stand overlooking the water, you hold your token of faith in one hand. You cannot help but feel that you were led astray. Taking a deep breath, you throw the token into the water below. As it sinks, you feel some part of yourself sink with it. There is no turning back now."
msgstr ""
"你站在桥上，俯瞰米斯卡塔尼克河，看底下的河水舞动闪光。你一回来，就感觉到情况不同了，有什么变了。跟你同一信仰的兄弟姐妹说，有穿着补丁长袍的外来者近日抵达，念叨着非凡的预言和诱人的承诺。你的信仰圣地现在已经盖满了异教的符号：手上长着喷火的眼睛、流出血的圣杯。你一度觉得神圣的东西已经毁了。"
"就现在你俯瞰水面的时候，手里还攥着你的信仰的信物。你不禁觉得自己被引入了歧途。你深吸一口气，将信物扔进水里。它沉没的时候，你感觉自己有一部分也随之沉没。现在已不能再回头了。"

msgid "Permanently remove the \"Walk in Faith\" Task from your deck and suffer 1 mental trauma. For the remainder of the campaign, you must treat the [elder_thing] token as if it were an [auto_fail] token, instead."
msgstr "将“追随信仰”任务从你的牌库永久移除，并承受1点精神创伤。你必须改为[elder_thing]标记视为如同[auto_fail]标记，直到剧本结束。"

msgid "Smirking, you walk away from your rendezvous with Sanford with a briefcase stuffed with bills. You skimmed enough ancient knick knacks and research notes to satisfy both Tillinghast and that old bat Sanford. With the payout from each of them, you have enough cash to go wherever you want, to be whomever you want to be. It sounds like Sanford and his lackeys are going under anyway."
msgstr "你得意地笑着，离开了和桑福德私会的地方，手里的公文包装满了钞票。你从那些远古的小玩意儿和研究笔记里搜刮出了一些东西，足以同时满足蒂林哈斯特和老不死的桑福德。他们给你的报酬，足以让你去任何想去的地方，成为任何想成为的人。听上去桑福德和他的喽啰们也混不长了。"

msgctxt "masculine"
msgid "#name# made bank."
msgstr "#name#大赚一笔。"

msgctxt "feminine"
msgid "#name# made bank."
msgstr "#name#大赚一笔。"

msgctxt "nonbinary"
msgid "#name# made bank."
msgstr "#name#大赚一笔。"

msgid ""
"Smirking, you walk away from your rendezvous with Sanford with a full briefcase. You turn a corner to find yourself surrounded by thugs."
"\"Tillinghast told us you were well overdue. Thankfully, I think you're ready to pay up,\" one of them says. Apparently, it was tougher to play both sides than you thought. Raising your fists, you brace yourself for what's about to come next. Hell, if you're going down, you're gonna go down swinging."
msgstr ""
"你得意地笑着，离开了和桑福德私会的地方，手里的公文包满满当当。你转过街角，发现自己被一群暴徒包围了。"
"“蒂林哈斯特告诉我们你有债没还。幸好，我感觉你已经准备还了。”其中一个说道。显然，当两面派比你想的要难多了。你举起拳头，准备面对接下来的一切。妈的，就算前功尽弃，你倒下之前也要做最后一搏。"

msgid "Permanently remove the \"Good Money\" Task from your deck and suffer 1 physical trauma. Search the collection for an [[Injury]] or [[Criminal]] basic weakness and add it to your deck. This card does not count toward your investigator's deck size."
msgstr "将“价值千金”任务从你的牌库永久移除，并承受1点肉体创伤。查找收藏，找出一张[[损伤]]或[[罪犯]]基础弱点，并将其加入你的牌库。这张卡牌不计入你的牌库卡牌张数。"

msgid "Remove the [elder_sign] token from the chaos bag for the remainder of the campaign."
msgstr "从混乱袋中移除1个[elder_sign]标记，直到剧本结束。"

msgid "Add a +1 token to the chaos bag for the remainder of the campaign."
msgstr "在混乱袋中加入1个+1标记，直到剧本结束。"

msgid "You leaf through Randall's reward for all your efforts: a tattered stack of Blavatsky and Crowley books. They might satisfy some fledgling seer, but not you. The fact that he offered them as a reward is almost insulting. Closing the book, you hear a faint whisper of the same voices you heard in R'lyeh. Your nightmares were not heralds of destruction: they were warnings from vagrant spirits. The coming calamity may be unavoidable, they tell you, but that doesn't mean you can't fight it."
msgstr "你翻阅着兰道尔给予你的所有奖赏：就是一堆破破烂烂的布拉瓦茨基和克劳利的著作（译者注：二人都是当时著名的神秘学家）。这或许能满足某些菜鸟预言师，但满足不了你。他把这些东西当作奖励，几乎就是侮辱。你合上书，听到一声低语，和你在拉莱耶听到的是一样的声音。你的留梦并非毁灭的预兆，而是流浪魂灵的警告。它们你说，即将到来的灾变也许无法避免，但这并不意味着你要束手就缚。"

msgctxt "masculine"
msgid "#name# understands the future."
msgstr "#name#明晓未来。"

msgctxt "feminine"
msgid "#name# understands the future."
msgstr "#name#明晓未来。"

msgctxt "nonbinary"
msgid "#name# understands the future."
msgstr "#name#明晓未来。"

msgid "The whispers that plagued you in R'lyeh have finally stopped. Since returning from R'lyeh, you wake up every morning to complete silence. Rather than console you, however, the lack of whispers fills you with even more dread. It is as if your link to the beyond has been severed. Or perhaps the spirits that wanted to warn you of the coming calamity have abandoned you."
msgstr "煎熬你前往拉莱耶的低语终于停了。自打从拉菜耶返回.你每天早上起来就是彻底的宁静。然而听不到低语并未让你欣慰，反而更加害怕。仿佛你与彼端的联系就此被切断。或者那些魂灵本来打算警告你即将到来的灾变，现在却遗弃了你。"

msgid "Permanently remove the \"Dreams of Destruction\" Task from your deck and suffer 1 mental trauma."
msgstr "将“毁灭之梦”任务从你的牌库永久移除，并承受1点精神创伤。"

msgid "You storm out of Tillinghast Esoterica, your head ringing with Randall's honeyed promises. Your debt was forgiven, but there is still the matter of your room and board to settle. \"Just a few more months, and we can finally settle up,\" he cooed. Rather than answer, you grabbed your reward and walked out. It was never about the money. He wanted to keep you on retainer. He'll surely be after you for the money eventually, but that doesn't matter now. You never needed him in the first place. Home is what you make it, not where you make it, there's nothing Tillinghast can do to take that from you now."
msgstr "你冲出蒂林哈斯特密所，耳畔还回响着兰道尔甜蜜的承诺。你的债务是被免除了，但还有安身之所的问题。“再有几个月，我们就能算清总账了。”他柔声说道。你没答复他，抓起报酬就走了。一直都不是钱的问题。他想把你图养起来。他最后肯定会为了钱来找你，但现在这不重要。你从一开始就不需要他。家是一个定义，而不是一个地方，蒂林哈斯特再也不能夺走你的家了。"

msgctxt "masculine"
msgid "#name# found his true home."
msgstr "#name#找到了真正的家。"

msgctxt "feminine"
msgid "#name# found her true home."
msgstr "#name#找到了真正的家。"

msgctxt "nonbinary"
msgid "#name# found their true home."
msgstr "#name#找到了真正的家。"

msgid ""
"You walk through Southside, reflecting on Randall's last words to you. Your debt was forgiven, but there is still the matter of your room and board to settle. \"Just a few more months, and we can finally settle up,\" he cooed. You thanked him. It's an entirely reasonable request. And after all, he's the only reason you're not living on the streets."
"Walking past Ma's Boarding House, you catch the scent of a home-cooked meal: fresh-baked bread, green beans, and sliced ham. Your stomach rumbles. You feel an old yearning, something more than hunger. Just a lttle more work, and Tillinghast will help you get your feet under you. Someday soon, you'll have a home of your own."
msgstr ""
"你走过南区，回想着兰道尔最后对你说的话。你的债务是被免除了，但还有安身之所的问题。“再有几个月，我们就能算清总账了。”他柔声说道。你谢过他，这要求合情合理。毕竟，你是因为他才没露宿街头。"
"你走过老马旅舍的时候，闻到了家常菜的味道：新烤的面包、绿绿的豆子，还有切好的火腿。你的肚子咕噜咕噜叫了起来。你感到一阵久违的渴望，这不仅仅是饥饿。只要再多干点，蒂林哈斯特就会帮你站稳脚跟。很快，你就会有自己的家了。"

msgid "Permanently remove the \"No Place Like Home\" Task from your deck and suffer 1 physical or 1 mental trauma."
msgstr "将“吾家可归”任务从你的牌库永久移除，并承受1点肉体创伤或1点精神创伤。"

msgid "Walking through Independence Square, you round a corner to see a figure slumped on the ground. You break into a sprint toward them as your mind floods with memories of the pilgrim in R'lyeh. Your stomach turns as you approach, hoping for a much less gruesome experience. She's still breathing. You can help her. Whatever trouble people find themselves in, you know you'll always be there to help."
msgstr "你走过独立广场，看到墙角有个人倒在地上。你脑海中涌起拉莱耶的朝圣者的记忆，赶紧大步冲了过去。你过去的路上腹内作痛，希望这次的经历别那么可怕。她还在呼吸，你能救她。无论人们有怎样的麻烦，你知道你总是能施以援手。"

msgctxt "masculine"
msgid "#name# swore an oath to protect others."
msgstr "#name#立誓保卫他人。"

msgctxt "feminine"
msgid "#name# swore an oath to protect others."
msgstr "#name#立誓保卫他人。"

msgctxt "nonbinary"
msgid "#name# swore an oath to protect others."
msgstr "#name#立誓保卫他人。"

msgid "You wake up suddenly in the middle of your first night back in Arkham. The cat perched on the end of your bed flees in surprise as you wipe cold sweat from your forehead. Echoes of the faces you left behind slowly fade, but you can't stop thinking about the dying man's last words: \"Mother.\" Your heartbeat slows as you stare out the window. Thoughts of what you could have done differently envelop you. You will never be able to save everyone. Is it even worth it to try?"
msgstr "你回到阿卡姆的第一夜，就睡到一半惊醒。你擦去额头的冷汗，床尾睡着的猫都被你吓跑了。你抛下的人的面容已经渐渐淡忘，但你忍不住想到那位濒死之人最后的话：“主母”。你望向窗外，心跳渐渐慢了下来。你的脑海里全是自己当初能不能做点别的。你再也救不了任何人了。还值得一试吗？"

msgid "Permanently remove the \"Do No Harm\" Task from your deck and suffer 1 mental trauma."
msgstr "将“医者仁心”任务从你的牌库永久移除，并承受1点精神创伤。"

msgid "\"You'll be in charge of overseeing the construction and eventual management of the new factory.\" Your new employer beams, sliding a crisp contract across the table. As you look out the window of your new office, you feel your heart swell. After your success with the expedition, Tillinghast mentioned his connections with the budding New Horizons Industries. Even though the meat-packing magnate has yet to break ground in Arkham, Randall has assured you that you will be well taken care of. All you need to do is sign on the dotted line."
msgstr "“就由你来负责监管新工厂的建设和最终运营。”你的新老板笑着把一份干净利落的合同推过桌子。你从自己的新办公室向窗外看去，内心满是喜悦。你成功完成了探险，蒂林哈斯特也跟他在新兴的新视野公司的人脉提了一句。尽管这家肉类加工巨头还没在阿卡姆动工，兰道尔也保证，你会得到好好照顾的。现在要做的就是签字。"

msgctxt "masculine"
msgid "#name# found new work."
msgstr "#name#有了新工作。"

msgctxt "feminine"
msgid "#name# found new work."
msgstr "#name#有了新工作。"

msgctxt "nonbinary"
msgid "#name# found new work."
msgstr "#name#有了新工作。"

msgid "The room goes silent when you enter. When you asked for your old job back, Tillinghast was more than happy to oblige. As your old supervisor chats away like you never left, you catch your old colleagues' nervous stares. Whatever small favors the shady businessman pulled must have worked. As you take your seat, you look out at the nervous colleagues you once called friends. You got everything you wanted, even your old desk. Why do you still feel so empty?"
msgstr "你走进来的时候，整个房间都安静了。你开口要回自己原来的工作，蒂林哈斯特居然非常高兴地答应了。你过去的上级畅所欲言，仿佛你从未离开，但你还是发现了过去后事紧张的眼神。阴险的生意佬给的小恩小惠肯定起了作用。你坐回自己的位子，望了望你曾经称为“朋友”的紧张同事。你已经拿回了你想要的一切，其至包括你过去的办公桌。为什么你还是感觉如此空虚？"

msgid "Permanently remove the \"Toe the Line\" Task from your deck and suffer 1 physical trauma."
msgstr "将“安分守己”任务从你的牌库永久移除，并承受1点肉体创伤。"

msgid "Draw tokens from the chaos bag at random until you have 2 non symbol tokens. Replace each of these tokens with a chaos token of a value 2 lower for the remainder of the campaign. (If you are unable to replace a token, repeat this process until a total of 2 chaos tokens have been replaced.)"
msgstr "从混乱袋中抽取标记，直到你抽到2个非符号标记。将这些标记替换为其原本数值-2的标记，直到剧本结束。（如果你有标记不能替换，重复此过程，直到总计替换了2个混乱标记。）"

msgid "Note: the app will ask you for the tokens sequentially, and only show those that are eligible to be swapped (due to token limits)."
msgstr "注意：APP将按顺序想你询问标记，且仅显示符合替换条件的标记（受标记数量限制）。"

msgid "It is several nights after your return to Arkham, and you are looking down on an adoring crowd. It's no surprise the expedition was a success. It's all because of you. And after promising Tillinghast a few paltry favors, you're getting the recognition you so richly deserve. Soon, you'll see to it that anyone who ever doubted you gets what they deserve, as well. Whoever said humility was a good thing?"
msgstr "你回来阿卡姆已经有几天了，你正低头看若崇拜的人群。毫无疑问这场探险大获成功，而这全是因为你。在答应7蒂林哈斯特一点无关紧要的小恩小惠之后，你获得了自己早就该得的认可。那么，你也要让那些怀疑过你的人得到他们应有的下场。谁说人还是要谦虚？"

msgctxt "masculine"
msgid "#name# pulled their weight."
msgstr "#name#尽了本分。"

msgctxt "feminine"
msgid "#name# pulled their weight."
msgstr "#name#尽了本分。"

msgctxt "nonbinary"
msgid "#name# pulled their weight."
msgstr "#name#尽了本分。"

msgid "On the night of your return, you find yourself ignominiously shut out of your old crowd. Tillinghast himself spread the worst kinds of rumors about you. What's worse is that they were all true. You were nothing but a burden on the expedition. You are the laughing stock of your circle. Nothing you've achieved was ever on your own merits. You're as worthless as they said you are."
msgstr "你回来的那天晚上，就发现自己可耻地被之前的圈子扫地出门。蒂林哈斯特散布了你最恶劣的流言；更恶劣的是，那都是真的。你只会给探险队拖后腿。你成了朋友圈里的笑柄。你获得的任何成就都不是自己的功劳。你就跟他们说的一样没用。"

msgid "Permanently remove the \"Prove Your Worth\" Task from your deck and suffer 1 mental trauma. Remove cards of level 1-5 from your deck worth a total of 10 or more experience <i>(remember to purchase new cards to maintain a legal deck size)</i>. You cannot purchase those cards again."
msgstr "将“证明价值”任务从你的牌库永久移除，并承受1点精神创伤。从你的牌库移除总计至少10点经验值的等级1-5的卡牌<i>（记住要购买新卡牌以维持满足需求的牌库卡牌张数）</i>。你不能再购买那些移除的卡牌。"

msgid ""
"Barely a week after returning, you receive a request from Miskatonic University to formally present your findings. The word 'tenure' has reached your ears more than once. Despite the incredible acclaim your studies have brought you, the prestige feels empty. The academic song and dance is little more than shadowplay. And it is nothing compared to the horrific truths you learned in R'lyeh. On more than one occasion, you find yourself awake in the dark, breathing heavily, with memories of a time and a world not your own. You know the horrible truth: Humanity is nothing more than a weak echo of far greater civilizations."
"Perhaps it is true. Perhaps you are nothing but a speck, and all your strivings are for naught. But you've also heard great things about Miskatonic's tenure package. You've earned it, damn it all. You may as well enjoy it."
msgstr ""
"你回来还不到一周，就收到米大的邀请，要正式介绍你的发现。“教职”这个词你也是听到不止一次了。尽管你的研究带来了难以置信的赞誉，但名望之后的感受还是空虚。学术界的夸夸其谈不过是一种皮影戏，没有什么能和你在拉莱耶发现的恐怖真相相比。你发现自己不止一次在黑暗中惊醒，气喘吁吁，脑子里全是不属于你这个时间这个世界的记忆。你知道可怕的真相：人类不过是更伟大文明的虚弱回响。"
"也许这是真的。也许你不过是一点尘埃，你所有的挣扎都是徒劳。但你也听说过米大教职的丰厚待遇。去他妈的，这是你应得的。你还不如好好享受一下。"

msgctxt "masculine"
msgid "#name# learned the secret truth."
